The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Varanasi, March 28 (PTI): Four persons were injured when a group allegedly opened fire on them at the cantonment railway station in Varanasi because of a dispute over a railway contract this morning.           One of the accused was caught on the spot and a search is on for his accomplices, police said. A scuffle had broken out between the two groups over bagging the contract, the police said.                   
	 Almora (PTI): A case has been registered against a schoolteacher for allegedly beating and abusing a student at Thiklana, 25km from Almora. The childs mother had complained Pratap Ram had severely beaten Thakur Singh, a Class V student.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has asked police to provide security to a newly-wed couple, who were allegedly threatened by their relatives and Jammu and Kashmir police because they are from different communities. Anjum Hussain and Khemraj married against their parents wishes.                  
	 Coimbatore (PTI): Security at the Coimbatore airport has been tightened after police got an email saying explosives would be planted at four airports in Tamil Nadu, which could go off any time. Erode superintendent of police said the mail said three persons would bring explosives in blue suitcases and plant them at the airports.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi police have got permission to arrest three accused, who are in judicial custody in connection with the murders of BPO employee Jigisha Ghosh and journalist Soumya Vishwanathan.
                                                                                                                           
